00:59.333 --> 01:01.166
♪ It's my life ♪

01:01.200 --> 01:02.300
♪ And my dream ♪

01:02.333 --> 01:06.233
<i>♪ And nothing's gonna</i>
<i>stop me now ♪</i>

01:15.733 --> 01:17.333
[instrumental music]

01:21.066 --> 01:24.466
"Attach lead wire‐C
to terminal‐D."

01:26.100 --> 01:27.766
Cousin, guess what today is?

01:27.800 --> 01:29.100
Wednesday?

01:29.133 --> 01:31.466
[mumbling]
Yes.

01:31.500 --> 01:33.300
But better than that.

01:33.333 --> 01:36.433
This is the day we found out
how to get rich.

01:36.466 --> 01:38.433
Just like Miss Elvira Worth.

01:38.466 --> 01:39.566
Who's Elvira Worth?

01:39.600 --> 01:42.566
More to the point,
what is Elvira Worth?

01:44.466 --> 01:46.566
Listen to this.
This come in the mail today.

01:46.600 --> 01:51.133
"Miss Elvira Worth, a housewife
from De Queen, Arkansas"

01:51.166 --> 01:53.766
turned a $500
investment‐‐"

01:53.800 --> 01:55.633
I can't understand
a word you're saying.

01:55.666 --> 01:58.133
"Miss Elvira Worth, a housewife
from De Queen, Arkansas

01:58.166 --> 01:59.300
turned a $500
investment‐‐"

01:59.333 --> 02:00.333
‐ "In the‐‐"
‐ "Stock market‐‐"

02:00.366 --> 02:01.400
‐ "Into‐‐"
‐ "Millions‐‐"

02:01.433 --> 02:02.433
‐ "Overnight‐‐"
‐ "We can‐‐"

02:02.466 --> 02:03.566
‐ "Too."
‐ Hm.

02:06.300 --> 02:08.133
Balki, leave your money
in the bank.

02:08.166 --> 02:10.566
Forget about the stock market.
You know nothing about it.

02:10.600 --> 02:13.566
Well, of course I do.
Don't be ridiculous.

02:15.366 --> 02:18.033
On Mypos, I sell my sheep
at the stock market.

02:19.366 --> 02:21.166
No.

02:21.200 --> 02:25.400
Balki, American stock markets
don't deal in livestock.

02:25.433 --> 02:29.700
The stocks they buy and sell
are shares in businesses.

02:29.733 --> 02:33.633
Oh. That sounds more exciting
than our stock market.

02:34.733 --> 02:37.000
I bet it smells
better, too, huh?

02:39.266 --> 02:41.100
Are there any
other pluses?

02:41.133 --> 02:43.666
Well, uh, yes,
there are.

02:43.700 --> 02:46.366
Depending on whether
the business makes money or not

02:46.400 --> 02:48.633
the value of your stock
goes up or down.

02:48.666 --> 02:52.000
Oh, I want the kinda
stock that goes up.

02:52.566 --> 02:54.000
That's very shrewd.

02:56.266 --> 02:57.766
But sometimes
your stock goes down.

02:57.800 --> 03:00.233
‐ No, I don't want that kind.
‐ No.

03:00.266 --> 03:01.633
No one does.

03:01.666 --> 03:03.733
Unfortunately,
there's no way of knowing

03:03.766 --> 03:05.366
whether your stock
will go up of down.

03:05.400 --> 03:07.600
Balki, I think you should forget
about the stock market.

03:07.633 --> 03:09.366
No, cousin, I want you
to help me buy stock.

03:09.400 --> 03:12.733
It's very complicated.
You could lose your shirt.

03:12.766 --> 03:16.200
Your money, your money,
you could lose your money.

03:16.233 --> 03:17.333
You're not going
to invest in the

03:17.366 --> 03:18.433
stock market
and that's that.

03:18.466 --> 03:20.200
Oh, that's that,
is that?

03:20.233 --> 03:23.333
Yes, that's that, I'm not going
to help you lose your money.

03:23.366 --> 03:25.800
Alright, fine.

03:25.833 --> 03:27.766
No skin off my head.

03:30.466 --> 03:33.233
I'll just go ask Mary Anne
to help me lose my money.

03:33.266 --> 03:34.733
Oh‐oh, wait, wait.

03:34.766 --> 03:37.300
You don't wanna ask Mary Anne.

03:37.333 --> 03:40.133
Alright, look, if you're
determined to do this

03:40.166 --> 03:41.333
I'll help you.

03:41.366 --> 03:43.300
‐ Oh, thank you, cousin.
‐ Hm.

03:46.133 --> 03:48.100
Now, here's
the business section.

03:49.433 --> 03:53.566
This is a listing
of all the stocks.

03:53.600 --> 03:55.600
Now, which one
do you wanna buy?

03:55.633 --> 03:57.333
There's so many.

03:57.366 --> 03:59.733
Oh, hey, here's one I've heard
good things about...

03:59.766 --> 04:01.300
...UniCorn.

04:01.333 --> 04:03.300
Oh, I like unicorns.

04:03.333 --> 04:05.500
You say that
they don't sell animals.

04:05.533 --> 04:07.733
You tried to fool Balki.

04:08.766 --> 04:12.166
UniCorn is
the United Corn Corporation.

04:12.200 --> 04:13.133
They make breakfast foods

04:13.166 --> 04:16.033
like, uh, Sugar Oatsies
and Raisin Puffs.

04:16.065 --> 04:18.466
Ooh, Raisin Puffs
are my favorite.

04:19.666 --> 04:22.200
♪ You get 100 raisins
in every box ♪

04:22.233 --> 04:24.166
♪ Of UniCorn
Raisin Puffs ♪

04:30.733 --> 04:33.033
How many shares
can I buy?

04:33.066 --> 04:35.133
Well, how much money
do you wanna invest?

04:36.800 --> 04:38.200
$38.

04:39.800 --> 04:41.266
$38.

04:41.300 --> 04:43.166
All this is for $38?

04:43.600 --> 04:44.700
And 10 cent.

04:46.533 --> 04:47.533
Alright, well...

04:47.566 --> 04:48.800
[clears throat]

04:48.833 --> 04:51.800
If I lend you $1.90,
you can buy one share.

04:51.833 --> 04:54.300
Oh‐oh, great!
We can be partners.

04:54.333 --> 04:56.433
No, no,
consider it a gift.

04:57.566 --> 05:00.066
Cousin,
isn't it wonderful?

05:00.100 --> 05:03.700
An hour ago, I was a babe
in the woodpile.

05:04.800 --> 05:07.166
I don't know nothing
about the stock market.

05:07.200 --> 05:09.133
And now, thanks to you

05:09.166 --> 05:12.333
I'm on my way to becoming
a business typhoon.

05:15.366 --> 05:18.100
Balki, a typhoon is a‐‐

05:18.133 --> 05:20.233
Tropical storm, I know that,
I was just kidding.

05:20.266 --> 05:23.233
Cut me
some slack, cousin.

05:23.266 --> 05:26.200
[instrumental music]

05:32.800 --> 05:34.300
[sighs]

05:34.333 --> 05:38.066
Balki, you don't have time
to play with the lint brush.

05:38.100 --> 05:39.700
Jennifer and Mary Anne
will be here any minute.

05:39.733 --> 05:41.766
We have reservations
for 8 o'clock.

05:41.800 --> 05:44.233
Cousin, I have
a surprise for you.

05:48.266 --> 05:50.733
I got my UniCorn
stock certificate.

05:58.166 --> 05:59.666
And you framed it.

06:02.233 --> 06:04.066
Yes, I did.

06:04.100 --> 06:05.466
Isn't it beautiful?

06:05.500 --> 06:07.366
Yes, it's brightens up
the whole room.

06:07.400 --> 06:08.366
Oh.

06:11.100 --> 06:12.100
Oh.

06:29.133 --> 06:31.133
Will you stop that?

06:31.166 --> 06:32.733
[doorbell buzzes]

06:32.766 --> 06:34.300
That's the girls.

06:40.500 --> 06:41.700
‐ Hi.
‐ Hi.

06:41.733 --> 06:44.566
I hope we're not late, I just
couldn't find anything to wear.

06:44.600 --> 06:48.700
You look stunning,
that's your color.

06:48.733 --> 06:51.233
Thank you. I borrowed
this outfit from Mary Anne.

06:51.266 --> 06:52.233
[chuckles]

06:53.333 --> 06:55.733
Jennifer and Mary Anne,
I have a surprise for you.

06:55.766 --> 06:57.733
Oh, don't tell me.
Let me guess?

07:02.833 --> 07:06.300
No sense hurting
yourself, Mary Anne.

07:06.333 --> 07:08.433
Why don't you just
let Balki tell us?

07:08.466 --> 07:11.366
Better yet, why don't
I just show you?

07:11.400 --> 07:12.433
Come on.

07:13.133 --> 07:13.966
Hurry up.

07:17.833 --> 07:19.366
This is it.

07:24.066 --> 07:25.566
[Mary]
What are we supposed
to be looking at?

07:27.300 --> 07:29.466
Balki just bought
his first share of stock

07:29.500 --> 07:31.100
in the
United Corn Corporation.

07:31.133 --> 07:33.733
I own a piece
of America.

07:33.766 --> 07:35.233
Congratulations.

07:35.266 --> 07:36.433
Oh, thank you.

07:36.466 --> 07:40.433
You know, we at UniCorn make
many fine products for the home.

07:43.433 --> 07:45.233
But the backbone
of our company

07:45.266 --> 07:47.000
is Raisin Puffs...

07:50.066 --> 07:54.300
...the cereal chock‐full
of naturally‐sweet raisins.

07:54.333 --> 07:57.033
Raisins. They're
nature's candy.

08:00.266 --> 08:01.266
I'll get my car keys

08:01.300 --> 08:02.433
and maybe we can
get out of here

08:02.466 --> 08:04.100
before he sings
the jingle.

08:05.200 --> 08:07.600
I used to eat Raisin Puffs
but I don't anymore.

08:07.633 --> 08:09.400
There aren't
enough raisins.

08:09.433 --> 08:12.200
[mumbles]
That's impossible.

08:12.233 --> 08:14.233
Raisin Puffs guarantees

08:14.266 --> 08:16.600
one hundred raisins
in every box.

08:16.633 --> 08:17.700
Look, I'll show you.

08:17.733 --> 08:22.500
Right on the box it says
"100 raisins in each box."

08:22.533 --> 08:24.633
So, you see, Raisin Puffs
without the raisins

08:24.666 --> 08:27.466
is like Snow White
without her seven dorks.

08:33.500 --> 08:36.100
Mary Anne may
have been mistaken.

08:36.133 --> 08:39.666
You bet your bottom digda
she was, look at this.

08:39.700 --> 08:41.000
See this?

08:44.600 --> 08:46.533
Where are the raisins?

08:47.766 --> 08:50.100
[chuckles]
There must be in here.

08:52.266 --> 08:53.633
Well, let's go.

08:57.266 --> 08:59.366
Why does Balki
have a box on his face?

09:00.633 --> 09:02.566
He lost
his raisins.

09:04.500 --> 09:06.400
Right, okay.
ladies, uh?

09:07.433 --> 09:09.166
Why...

09:09.200 --> 09:11.033
...would my company do this?

09:12.366 --> 09:15.600
Why would they say that they
put 100 raisins in every box

09:15.633 --> 09:19.600
and then they don't put
100 raisins in every box?

09:19.633 --> 09:22.566
Well, maybe this is a signal
to sell your stock, Balki.

09:24.666 --> 09:26.133
[Balki
They must be in here.

09:27.333 --> 09:29.066
Maybe they're all down
at the bottom.

09:29.100 --> 09:31.300
Bal‐Balki, what...
What are you doing?

09:31.333 --> 09:33.433
Remember,
we have reservations.

09:33.466 --> 09:36.166
Cousin, I'm in the middle
of a company crisis.

09:37.700 --> 09:38.700
I don't know
what you're doing

09:38.733 --> 09:40.600
but couldn't
you do it later?

09:40.633 --> 09:42.633
No, cousin, please,
you go to the restaurant

09:42.666 --> 09:44.133
with Jennifer and Mary Anne

09:44.166 --> 09:46.500
and I come to you
when I'm finished.

09:46.533 --> 09:49.166
Well, uh, let's go
to the restaurant

09:49.200 --> 09:50.566
and Balki can join us

09:50.600 --> 09:53.300
whenever he's finished
his, uh...

09:53.333 --> 09:54.166
...raisin count.

09:54.200 --> 09:57.766
Two, three, four,
five, six, seven.

09:57.800 --> 09:59.633
Please let there be 100.

10:02.733 --> 10:05.666
[instrumental music]

10:15.666 --> 10:17.733
One, two

10:17.766 --> 10:19.266
three, four...

10:19.300 --> 10:21.100
Balki, you're here.

10:21.133 --> 10:22.800
‐ Six‐‐
‐ Where have you been?

10:22.833 --> 10:24.666
‐ Seven... shh‐‐
‐ I called from the restaurant.

10:24.700 --> 10:26.666
There was no answer,
I don't know how many times

10:26.700 --> 10:28.733
that might have ring,
15, 16‐‐

10:28.766 --> 10:31.700
17, 18, 19...

10:35.800 --> 10:38.566
Cousin, uh,
I was at the store.

10:40.433 --> 10:41.400
One...

10:43.266 --> 10:45.400
Oh, my Lord.

10:45.433 --> 10:49.200
Balki, how many boxes
of Raisin Puffs have you opened?

10:49.233 --> 10:50.133
..eight‐‐

10:50.166 --> 10:52.700
‐ One, two, three, four‐‐
‐ Nine, ten‐‐

10:52.733 --> 10:55.066
Five, six, seven,
eight, nine

10:55.100 --> 10:56.400
‐ Ten, eleven, twelve‐‐
‐ Ten, eleven, twelve‐‐

10:56.433 --> 10:57.533
‐ Thirteen.
‐ thirteen.

11:05.200 --> 11:09.466
Cousin, I have opened
13 boxes of Raisin Puffs

11:09.500 --> 11:13.500
and not one of them has
even close to 100 raisins.

11:13.533 --> 11:16.433
Oh, I'm so disheveled!

11:17.800 --> 11:20.300
My new family
has been cheating the public.

11:20.333 --> 11:22.600
Family? What family?

11:22.633 --> 11:24.500
The UniCorn family.

11:24.533 --> 11:27.166
Mr. Henry Casselman
the chairman of the board

11:27.200 --> 11:28.800
writes me a letter
and tells me

11:28.833 --> 11:30.533
I'm the newest member
of the family.

11:32.400 --> 11:33.733
Balki, this is
a form letter.

11:33.766 --> 11:36.033
But it does have
a nice shape.

11:36.066 --> 11:38.600
Families don't
send form letters.

11:38.633 --> 11:40.266
Businesses do.

11:40.300 --> 11:42.366
Cold, impersonal companies

11:42.400 --> 11:44.133
who're only interested
in the bottom line

11:44.166 --> 11:45.300
making a buck.

11:45.333 --> 11:48.466
Balki, you're letting the stock
thing take over your life.

11:48.500 --> 11:50.700
This is not
your responsibility.

11:50.733 --> 11:52.066
Yes, it is.

11:52.100 --> 11:53.500
On Mypos, when you're
on the business

11:53.533 --> 11:56.166
you're are responsible
for everything.

11:56.200 --> 11:57.733
Oh! Oh!

11:57.766 --> 12:00.066
I just had
a terrific idea.

12:00.100 --> 12:01.433
Why don't you just
sell your stock

12:01.466 --> 12:02.300
and forget
the whole thing.

12:02.333 --> 12:05.066
‐ I can't.
‐ Okay, then I'll sell it.

12:05.100 --> 12:06.366
‐ No.
‐ Then I'll buy it.

12:06.400 --> 12:08.466
Balki, please, I'm hungry.

12:08.500 --> 12:11.033
I just want to go back to
the restaurant and have dinner.

12:11.066 --> 12:12.366
Cousin, you don't understand.

12:12.400 --> 12:14.300
I have to
make this right.

12:14.333 --> 12:16.366
How‐how, how are
you gonna do that?

12:16.400 --> 12:19.166
I'll... go to UniCorn

12:19.200 --> 12:21.433
and I tell them they have
to stop cheating the public.

12:21.466 --> 12:24.200
Okay, tell who?
Balki, tell who?

12:24.233 --> 12:26.266
UniCorn is
a big corporation.

12:26.300 --> 12:27.766
They have thousands
of employees.

12:27.800 --> 12:28.800
Who are you
gonna talk to?

12:28.833 --> 12:30.733
Oh, who am I going
to talk to?

12:30.766 --> 12:32.266
Who are you going
to talk to?

12:32.300 --> 12:34.600
I am going to talk to

12:34.633 --> 12:39.333
the man who puts raisins
in the boxes.

12:39.366 --> 12:40.400
Wrong!

12:42.233 --> 12:43.700
He takes his orders
from his foreman.

12:43.733 --> 12:46.433
Well, then I'll go
to his four men.

12:46.466 --> 12:48.200
And they'll send you
to the plant manager.

12:48.233 --> 12:50.400
Well, now we're
getting somewhere.

12:50.433 --> 12:52.166
No, no, we are not.

12:52.200 --> 12:55.566
Balki, Balki, UniCorn
is a huge corporation.

12:55.600 --> 12:57.400
They have factories
all over the world.

12:57.433 --> 12:59.533
They have layers
of authority.

12:59.566 --> 13:01.800
The plant managers will send you
to the district manager

13:01.833 --> 13:03.466
and he'll send you
to the regional manager.

13:03.500 --> 13:05.666
You'll talk to
treasurers, controllers

13:05.700 --> 13:08.033
assistant vice presidents,
second vice presidents

13:08.066 --> 13:09.066
first vice presidents.

13:09.100 --> 13:10.366
And this doesn't
make any difference

13:10.400 --> 13:11.700
because they all
take their orders

13:11.733 --> 13:13.333
from the chairman
of the board.

13:13.366 --> 13:14.533
Well, then
I'll go see him.

13:14.566 --> 13:16.266
He won't see you.

13:20.366 --> 13:22.366
Why you make me go see
all those other people?

13:22.400 --> 13:24.466
To teach you a lesson.

13:25.700 --> 13:27.133
This is hopeless, Balki.

13:27.166 --> 13:30.033
You are only one man
with one share.

13:30.066 --> 13:31.433
They won't listen.

13:31.466 --> 13:33.466
Well, cousin

13:33.500 --> 13:34.666
if you come with me

13:34.700 --> 13:37.366
we'll be two men
with one share.

13:38.600 --> 13:41.333
And then they will
have to listen.

13:41.366 --> 13:43.033
Huh, uh, oh.

13:49.666 --> 13:51.233
[instrumental music]

13:58.736 --> 14:00.130
I want to see
Mr. Casselman.

14:00.164 --> 14:01.264
Do you have an appointment?

14:01.297 --> 14:03.497
‐ No.
‐ Then you can't see him.

14:05.197 --> 14:07.064
Thank you for your help.

14:09.197 --> 14:11.030
Can he
make an appointment?

14:11.064 --> 14:13.130
Only through
the appointment secretary.

14:13.164 --> 14:16.097
‐ Can I see her?
‐ Not without an appointment.

14:17.930 --> 14:19.097
‐ Come on.
‐ No, no‐‐

14:19.130 --> 14:20.230
‐ Come on. Come on.
‐ Cousin, cousin, I‐‐

14:20.264 --> 14:21.930
Balki, I'll buy you
some ice cream.

14:28.030 --> 14:30.330
No, cousin.

14:30.364 --> 14:31.397
No.

14:31.430 --> 14:32.564
The public
is being cheated

14:32.597 --> 14:34.297
and if I don't
do something about it

14:34.330 --> 14:35.397
I'm cheating them, too.

14:35.430 --> 14:37.364
I know, Mr. Casselman
will understand

14:37.397 --> 14:39.230
if I can just
talk to him.

14:39.264 --> 14:42.164
Did you come here to help me
or to see me fail?

14:44.364 --> 14:46.564
Alright, alright.

14:46.597 --> 14:48.564
But if you're
really gonna see this guy

14:48.597 --> 14:50.830
we're gonna have
to use subterfuge.

14:50.864 --> 14:54.430
Well, of course we are.
Don't be ridiculous.

14:56.130 --> 14:58.330
Do you have some on you?

15:01.897 --> 15:06.897
Balki, subterfuge is just
a big word for sneakiness.

15:18.030 --> 15:19.364
[clears throat]

15:19.397 --> 15:21.497
Excuse me, I think there's been
a misunderstanding.

15:21.530 --> 15:24.364
Even though Mr. Bartokomous
doesn't have an appointment

15:24.397 --> 15:26.864
I'm sure, Mr. Casselman
will want to see him.

15:26.897 --> 15:29.897
Mr. Bartokomous is
a substantial stockholder.

15:29.930 --> 15:31.264
My car, Ms. Abrams.

15:31.297 --> 15:34.130
Mr. Casselman, I want to see you
I come to talk to you.

15:34.164 --> 15:36.997
I'm not Mr. Casselman.
I'm Mr. Crocker.

15:37.030 --> 15:38.164
I'm Lawrence Appleton

15:38.197 --> 15:40.497
and this is one of
your major stockholders.

15:40.530 --> 15:43.397
Balki Aristotle Bartokomous.

15:45.097 --> 15:47.497
Of the Mediterranean
Bartokomouses.

15:47.530 --> 15:50.130
Do you ever hear
of my little island Mypos?

15:50.164 --> 15:51.964
You have an island?

15:51.997 --> 15:54.497
Well, I'm always happy
to meet a major stockholder.

15:54.530 --> 15:56.097
[laughing]

15:56.130 --> 15:59.230
Care for some coffee,
cappuccino, espresso, eh?

16:00.030 --> 16:01.764
Are you the waiter?

16:04.530 --> 16:06.464
No, I'm executive
vice president

16:06.497 --> 16:08.197
soon to be top dog.

16:08.230 --> 16:10.230
Oh.

16:10.264 --> 16:13.364
What are you now,
deputy dog?

16:17.197 --> 16:18.797
[laughing]

16:18.830 --> 16:20.797
Uh, coffee will do.

16:20.830 --> 16:21.864
Ms. Abrams, please.

16:21.897 --> 16:23.064
And uh...

16:23.097 --> 16:24.097
...use the china.

16:24.130 --> 16:26.230
[Ms. Abrams]
Yes, sir.

16:26.264 --> 16:28.964
Uh, Mr. Bartokomous is here
to see Mr. Casselman.

16:28.997 --> 16:30.430
Oh, you can deal with me, uh.

16:30.464 --> 16:33.030
I'm taking over for him
when he retires, uh.

16:33.064 --> 16:34.830
Gentlemen, please.

16:35.997 --> 16:38.497
Now, then, what seems
to be the problem?

16:38.530 --> 16:40.030
Raisins.

16:40.064 --> 16:40.964
Raisins?

16:40.997 --> 16:43.797
There are not enough raisins
in Raisin Puffs.

16:43.830 --> 16:45.564
But I'm sure, this is a matter
of Mr. Bartokomous

16:45.597 --> 16:47.464
should be taking this up
with Mr. Casselman.

16:47.497 --> 16:49.564
Oh‐oh, uh‐uh, how many
shares did you say you own?

16:49.597 --> 16:50.430
One‐‐

16:50.464 --> 16:53.030
Hundred thousand.
One hundred thousand.

16:54.830 --> 16:56.564
Well, no, one share.

16:56.597 --> 16:58.197
One share?

16:58.230 --> 16:59.330
Is this a joke?

17:00.430 --> 17:02.564
Uh, ye‐yes!

17:02.597 --> 17:03.964
[chuckles]

17:03.997 --> 17:05.564
It's a joke.

17:05.597 --> 17:08.030
But, but Mr. Bartokomous

17:08.064 --> 17:10.930
is an internationally
known cut‐up.

17:10.964 --> 17:12.329
‐ Cousin.
‐ No, stop.

17:12.364 --> 17:14.097
‐ Cousin.
‐ Stop...

17:14.130 --> 17:16.864
[laughing]

17:16.896 --> 17:18.530
Now, if we can just
move this along.

17:18.564 --> 17:20.896
Mr. Casselman can give
Mr. Bartokomous five minutes

17:20.930 --> 17:24.164
and we can be off to our dinner
at the White House.

17:29.364 --> 17:32.764
Cousin, you said sneaky
but this is lying.

17:34.164 --> 17:35.997
‐ I only have one share.
‐ Uh.

17:36.030 --> 17:37.430
But I think
this is very important.

17:37.464 --> 17:38.997
And I want to see
Mr. Casselman.

17:39.030 --> 17:40.197
Here's the coffee.

17:40.230 --> 17:41.530
Forget the coffee.
Get security.

17:41.564 --> 17:43.797
Yes, sir.

17:43.830 --> 17:45.330
No, we're friends
with Mr. Casselman.

17:45.364 --> 17:47.230
Look, he write me a letter.

17:47.264 --> 17:48.864
Casselman sends out
millions of these.

17:48.897 --> 17:49.997
They're written
by machines.

17:50.030 --> 17:51.897
Mr. Crocker, this man
has put his trust

17:51.930 --> 17:53.497
and his faith
in your company.

17:53.530 --> 17:54.997
Doesn't that
mean anything to you?

17:55.030 --> 17:55.997
No.

17:57.264 --> 17:58.964
Here they are.

17:58.997 --> 18:00.164
Throw these two out.

18:00.197 --> 18:03.564
No, we just want to see
Mr. Casselman for five minutes.

18:03.597 --> 18:05.464
Come on you guys,
we don't wanna hurt you.

18:05.497 --> 18:07.897
I don't... we don't
want to be hurt.

18:09.064 --> 18:10.230
Let's go.

18:10.264 --> 18:14.964
‐ No, cousin, I don't like this.
‐ Huh.

18:14.997 --> 18:17.830
‐ Do something.
‐ Balki, we took our best shot.

18:19.930 --> 18:22.964
[sighs]
Not enough raisins. Really.

18:22.997 --> 18:23.997
[chuckles]

18:25.297 --> 18:26.897
[gasps]

18:26.930 --> 18:27.897
Mr. Casselman!

18:27.930 --> 18:30.197
Mr. Casselman, you're wanted
in the outer office.

18:30.230 --> 18:31.997
[Larry]
Mr. Casselman, you're wanted
in the outer office.

18:32.030 --> 18:32.997
Balki!

18:39.464 --> 18:42.130
[chuckles]
Oh, for crying out loud.

18:43.097 --> 18:44.064
[screaming]

18:45.964 --> 18:48.197
Mr. Casselman!
Mr. Casselman!

18:48.230 --> 18:50.930
Mr. Casselman, you're wanted
in the outer office.

18:50.964 --> 18:52.197
Balki!

18:52.230 --> 18:54.197
[grunting]

18:56.930 --> 18:57.864
[gasps]

19:01.964 --> 19:03.964
[grunting]

19:04.364 --> 19:05.297
No!

19:06.497 --> 19:08.430
[groaning]

19:12.097 --> 19:14.297
What the hell
is going on in here?

19:14.330 --> 19:16.030
Would you like
some coffee Mr. Casselman?

19:16.064 --> 19:17.064
‐ No!
‐ Oh!

19:17.097 --> 19:19.164
This is nothing
to concern yourself with, HC.

19:19.197 --> 19:21.230
Mr. Casselman,
we come to see you.

19:22.197 --> 19:23.397
Do I know you?

19:23.430 --> 19:25.097
Well, you sent me a letter.

19:26.197 --> 19:27.797
Oh.

19:27.830 --> 19:29.230
You're one of
our stockholders.

19:29.264 --> 19:31.130
He only
owns one share, HC.

19:31.164 --> 19:32.964
He's still
a stockholder.

19:32.997 --> 19:34.930
Good point, HC.

19:34.964 --> 19:36.830
Why did you
come to see about?

19:36.864 --> 19:39.330
There are no enough raisins
in Raisin Puffs.

19:39.364 --> 19:42.064
Ha, you, you want
more than a 100?

19:42.097 --> 19:44.430
To what he means is
there aren't a 100 in each box.

19:44.464 --> 19:45.264
And he can prove it.

19:45.297 --> 19:47.264
What do you want us
to do, count them?

19:47.297 --> 19:49.064
[laughing]

19:49.097 --> 19:50.797
We‐we can do that.

19:55.497 --> 19:58.197
I have only forty one.

19:58.230 --> 19:59.997
Forty nine here.

20:00.030 --> 20:00.997
Thirty eight.

20:01.030 --> 20:05.030
Forty four and the four
I eat makes forty eight.

20:05.064 --> 20:06.264
This is outrageous.

20:06.297 --> 20:07.864
I promised the public

20:07.897 --> 20:09.897
One hundred raisins
in every box.

20:09.930 --> 20:12.830
Who's responsible for this?

20:12.864 --> 20:15.430
Who's responsible
for this?

20:18.030 --> 20:19.864
So I skimped
a little on the raisins.

20:19.897 --> 20:21.197
I saved the company
a bundle.

20:21.230 --> 20:22.297
‐ Crocker.
‐ Yes, sir.

20:22.330 --> 20:24.564
‐ Put those raisins back!
‐ But, sir the savings‐‐

20:24.597 --> 20:27.030
‐ Put them back!
‐ Yes, sir. Good idea, sir.

20:27.064 --> 20:29.164
And apologize
to. Mr. Bartokomous.

20:29.197 --> 20:31.164
‐ But sir...
‐ Apologize.

20:31.197 --> 20:32.430
I'm sorry,
Mr. Bartokomous.

20:32.464 --> 20:34.564
Please accept
my apology.

20:34.597 --> 20:36.264
Oh, it's okay.

20:36.297 --> 20:38.464
To forgive is divine.

20:40.830 --> 20:43.297
To be an airhead
is human.

20:55.030 --> 20:57.497
Why my daughter
married that nitwit

20:57.530 --> 21:00.130
I'll never know.

21:00.164 --> 21:02.230
‐ Does anybody want any coffee?
‐ No!

21:02.264 --> 21:03.230
[Balki and Larry]
No, thank you.

21:03.264 --> 21:05.130
I don't know,
why I bother.

21:07.430 --> 21:10.464
I'm really glad you brought
this to my attention, son.

21:12.030 --> 21:13.864
He called me son.

21:13.897 --> 21:17.064
A lot of people think business
is cold and impersonal.

21:17.097 --> 21:19.330
All we're interested in
is making a buck.

21:19.364 --> 21:22.297
Uh, that thought never
crossed our minds.

21:24.497 --> 21:27.464
Well, that thought
never crossed his mind.

21:31.230 --> 21:33.197
Would you
do me a favor?

21:33.230 --> 21:35.464
Would you sign
my form letter?

21:35.497 --> 21:38.030
Oh, I'd be
happy to, son.

21:44.164 --> 21:46.464
Have you boys

21:46.497 --> 21:48.430
ever seen the city

21:48.464 --> 21:49.830
from a helicopter?

21:51.097 --> 21:52.864
Well, no.

21:52.897 --> 21:53.830
Too bad.

21:56.830 --> 21:58.830
Kidding! Ha, ha.

21:58.864 --> 22:02.264
Just because I'm rich,
doesn't mean I'm not a fun guy.

22:03.597 --> 22:05.130
What do you say

22:05.164 --> 22:08.430
we go buzz
the Kellogg Factory?

22:08.464 --> 22:10.297
[laughing]

22:10.330 --> 22:13.264
[instrumental music]

22:15.297 --> 22:17.997
[Larry]
You know, Balki,
that Casselman's a fun guy.

22:18.030 --> 22:19.797
You know about
the best part?

22:19.830 --> 22:21.897
Racing the police helicopter?

22:21.930 --> 22:22.964
That was fun.

22:22.997 --> 22:25.830
But no cousin, the best part was
that, thanks to you

22:25.864 --> 22:30.264
America is going to have raisins
coming out of her ears.

22:30.297 --> 22:31.464
What do you mean?
Thanks to me?

22:31.497 --> 22:33.564
I was the guy, who said one man
couldn't make a difference.

22:33.597 --> 22:34.730
And I was wrong
about that.

22:34.764 --> 22:38.397
Well, yes, you did but you were
also the man that said

22:38.430 --> 22:39.530
"If you want
to change something

22:39.564 --> 22:41.197
you gotta go the top guy."

22:41.230 --> 22:44.830
Hm‐m‐m, no, I think I said

22:44.864 --> 22:47.197
"If you get to the top guy
he'd throw you out."

22:47.230 --> 22:48.530
Well, you sure did.

22:48.564 --> 22:50.897
But you're also
the man that said

22:50.930 --> 22:53.464
"You've got
to use subterfuge."

22:53.497 --> 22:55.297
Which didn't work at all.

22:57.897 --> 22:58.697
You're not going
to let me say

22:58.730 --> 23:01.530
anything nice
about you, are you?

23:01.564 --> 23:02.530
Alright, go ahead.

23:02.564 --> 23:03.864
That's it.

23:06.830 --> 23:09.264
Could you, say it again.
I missed it.

23:09.297 --> 23:10.997
Cousin, it's simple.

23:11.030 --> 23:13.230
If you hadn't told me
what not to do

23:13.264 --> 23:16.364
I would never have known
what I should have been doing.

23:16.397 --> 23:18.064
And because you
came with me

23:18.097 --> 23:20.297
to stop me from doing
what I wanted to do

23:20.330 --> 23:22.064
but should not
have been doing.

23:22.097 --> 23:24.130
I was able to do,
what had to be done

23:24.164 --> 23:26.230
even though you didn't
want me to do it.

23:31.464 --> 23:33.264
Well, I'm glad
I could help.

23:45.864 --> 23:47.264
[theme music]
